FBIS4-9414 "dreeu080_p_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-080 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 POLAND Reportage on New Freedom Union Party Reportage on New Freedom Union Party Says Rebirth Process `Under Threat' LD2404122294 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1107 GMT 24 Apr 94 LD2404122294 Warsaw PAP Polish BFN [Text] Warsaw, 24 Apr--The congress of the Freedom Union adopted a resolution today that says the process of rebirth of the state and its economy, initiated in 1989, is under threat. The congress obliged the party authorities to prepare a strategy for "the second step along the road of reforms in Poland." The national congress found essential the earliest possible setting up of specialized secretariats to analyze the situation in particular spheres of social and economic life. "Their joint task would be to formulate the strategy of the second step along the road of reforms in Poland and winning its allies' and social partners' support for it," the resolution reads. People heading these secretariats would constitute a sort of "shadow cabinet."
